    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you need <code>Set</code> rather than <code>List</code>, you can use <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/EnumSet.html#allOf(java.lang.Class)\" rel=\"noreferrer\">EnumSet.allOf()</a>.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Set&lt;EnumerationClass&gt; set = EnumSet.allOf(EnumerationClass.class);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>Update</strong>: JakeRobb is right. My answer is about java.lang.Enum instead of java.util.Enumeration. Sorry for unrelated answer.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 476761,
      "reputation" : 25951,
      "user_id" : 887836,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 96,
