    "last_edit_date" : 1492519895,
    "creation_date" : 1492519164,
    "answer_id" : 43472429,
    "question_id" : 5610822,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>When using guava (See <a href=\"https://google.github.io/guava/releases/snapshot/api/docs/com/google/common/collect/Iterators.html#forEnumeration-java.util.Enumeration-\" rel=\"noreferrer\">doc</a>) there is <code>Iterators.forEnumeration</code>. Given an <code>Enumeration x</code> you can do the following:</p>\n\n<p>to get a immutable Set:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ImmutableSet.copyOf(Iterators.forEnumeration(x));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>to get a immutable List:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ImmutableList.copyOf(Iterators.forEnumeration(x));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>to get a hashSet:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Sets.newHashSet(Iterators.forEnumeration(x));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
